61a46987092f11ebbdaeac1f6bf848b6.annotations: Polish-Russian War (film) is a 2009 Polish film directed by Xawery Żuławski based on the novel Polish-Russian War under the white-red flag by Dorota Masłowska.

long_answer.0: The Civil Liberties Act of 1988 is a United States federal law that granted reparations to Japanese Americans who had been interned by the United States government during World War II.
long_answer.1: In the act, the blame for the internment of U.S. citizens was placed on the people of the United States, by apologizing on behalf of them.
